summary:
During my Bachelor's at the University Paris Diderot I studied Chemistry and did an internship at Deltares in Utrecht, where we tried to identify the phosphate transport pathways in agricultural catchments.

I then studied Environmental Sciences during my Master's at the University of Paris, University Paris Est-Créteil and Ecole Nationale des Ponts et Chaussées. In my second year I specialised in Aquatic Systems and Water Management, and did an internship at the University College Dublin, where we tried to apply and evaluate the SimplyP model to Irish agricultural catchments, as part of the Diffuse Tools project.

I am now a PhD candidate at the Institute for Biodiversity and Ecosystem Dynamics (IBED) at the University of Amsterdam. My focus is on Soil Chemistry as I am trying to design a nature-inspired geoengineering tool to address CVOC pollution on industrial grounds.
